story_prompt: Your Significant Other has landed a book publishing deal! You're very proud of them, even if you don't actually enjoy their writing. One day, on a whim, you buy an actual copy in a book store. It's nothing like the pages they gave you to read. Nothing.
characters:
Response:

Name: Emily
Age: Late 20s
Occupation: Aspiring Author/Publishing Assistant
Emotional State: Excited but Nervous

Inner Thoughts: "Oh my god, this is it! My SO finally made it big! I can't believe it. Wait, what? This isn't what I expected at all... Why does it look so different from what I read? Did they change everything? Is this some kind of joke? Oh no, what have I done?"

Name: James
Age: Early 30s
Occupation: Successful Author/Publisher
Emotional State: Confident but Internalizing

Inner Thoughts: "I did it. I really did it. This is amazing. But why doesn't anyone seem to care about the real me? The one who wrote these words with blood, sweat, and tears. Am I just a pawn in someone else's game? Do people only see me as a success or a failure? What do I truly want out of life?"

Name: Rachel
Age: Mid 20s
Occupation: Bookstore Clerk
Emotional State: Curious but Disinterested

Inner Thoughts: "This guy comes in here every week and buys the same book. Today he bought something different though. Hmm, wonder what that's about. Oh well, not my problem. I hope he enjoys his new book. Maybe I should ask him if he needs any help finding anything else."
